article.headline: Hawaii 93, Long Beach St. 78
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Riley Luettgerodt had career highs of 23 points, eight assists and four steals Saturday night as Hawaii rallied for a 93-78 victory over Long Beach State. Matt Lojeski added 22 points in the Bracket Buster game, which ended Long Beach State's five-game winning streak. Ahmet Gueye added 16 points and Matt Gibson had 15 points, a career-best 12 rebounds and six assists for the Rainbow Warriors (15-12), who shot 56 percent. Bobby Nash also scored 15 points. Aaron Nixon scored 17 points for the 49ers (18-7). Sterling Byrd added 16 points and Kejuan Johnson had 15 points and five assists.
